success.question_text: What is the mode of the scores 5, 7, 5, 4, 8, 6 and 9?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Chance and Data / Mean, Mode and Median

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

There are two scores of 5 and only one of each other score.

The mode is 5.

Tip

The mode is the score with the highest frequency. It is the score that occurs the most.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

If an event cannot happen the probability is 0. If it must happen the probability is 1. All other probabilities are between 0 and 1.

success.question_text: Which score could be left out without affecting the mean?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Chance and Data / Mean, Mode and Median

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

If a score equal to the mean is omitted from a set of scores, the mean will not change. If a score less than the mean is omitted, the mean will increase, and, if a score greater than the mean is omitted, the mean will decrease. For example, in this question if a score of 6 was left out, the remaining eight scores would add to 57 and the mean would increase to 7.125. If a score of 9 was left out, the remaining eight scores would add to 54 and the mean would decrease to 6.75.

success.question_text: Which set of scores has the greatest median?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Chance and Data / Mean, Mode and Median

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

The median is the middle score when the scores are arranged in order. If there is an even number of scores, the median is the average of the two middle scores.

Tip

A travel graph shows the distance a traveller is from a certain point at different times. At any given time a traveller can only be one distance from that point.

Tip

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

Consider each option.

If a coin is tossed twice there are four outcomes; head head, head tail, tail head or tail tail. The probability of two heads is 1 in 4 (or 0.25).

There are six outcomes when throwing a die. The probability of 5 is 1 in 6 (or 0.1666…).

The prime numbers less than 10 are 2, 3, 5 and 7. The probability of choosing a prime number is 4 in 9 (or 0.4444…).

There are four suits in a pack of playing cards: hearts, diamonds, spades and clubs. The probability of choosing a heart is 1 in 4 (or 0.25).

The lowest probability is 1 in 6.

Of the options, the lowest probability is for ‘Getting 5 when throwing a die.’

review_2.column_1_text:
Tip

The probability of an event is equal to the number of times that event can occur out of the total number of possible outcomes. Probability is usually given as a fraction but can be expressed as a decimal or percentage.
